locality: Following the mule trail between Inquisivi and the Río Khatu Bridge ca. 1-3 km N of Inquisivi. Semi-arid to seasonally humid forests.
Khora Pata - - On the slopes 1-2 km SW of Communidad Khora. 28 km N. of Choquetanga. Spiny dense woodland and mattoral with Acacia, Tabebuia, tree Opuntias, Bombaceae and Malphigiaceae abundant.

Lakachaka to Samaipata - - This is our famous camp at the mouth of the Río Aguilani on extensive ancient agriculture terraces, where are two foot bridges. Collections made along the trail to Khora between Laka Chaka and the old Inca cemetary at Samaipata about 4 km of trail collected, 21 km N of Choquetanga. On slopes above river.
Parque Estadual do Ibitipoca, Gruta dos três Arcos.

5 km N of YPFB Gas Plant on the Rio Grande, 1 km S of road Brecha 5-1/2. Remnants of deciduous Chaco scrub forest, with Tabebuia nodosa, Capparis spp., Diplokeleba floribunda, flat, sandy, almost entirely cleared for agriculatural fields by the Mennonites.
